current.goal_statement: Great work tracking your goals! Here is a summary of your recent progress:

results.text: Great work eating vegetables for breakfast.
Great job logging your beverage intake. Staying hydrated is important for proper organ function, body temperature regular, digestion, and maintaining healthy skin, just to name a few.

You could try experimenting with noodles made from different types of flour or grains (e.g. whole grain noodles, whole wheat noodles, brown rice noodles, quinoa or spelt pasta). You can mix half white and half whole grain noodles together and increase the whole grain type over time to transition to suit your preferences!

Consider swapping out foods or ingredients high in saturated and trans fats like red meats, bakery products, and hard margarines with unsaturated fats. Instead, try foods such as hemp hearts, flax seeds, nuts (like walnuts), seeds (like sunflower seeds), avocado, fish, and some oils (like olive, canola or safflower). Some of the fried foods you ate may include shrimp tempura; spring roll; fried chicken; hash brown patty; fried egg; home fries; fried tofu; fried octopus. If possible, try grilling or baking instead.
